<br>
At some point soon, we can no longer get upgrades from static mobs.  The planes, ToV, Umbral ...soon the people that raid often with us will have everything they can get from these places (I know I do, but there's not much out there for a monk in these places).  This means we have to set our sights on bigger and better things.<br>
<br>
Unfortunatly, these bigger and better things don't come easy.  We can't plan to raid Zlandicar on any given sunday, because the chances are far better than not that he won't be up.  Same goes for just about any boss or mini-boss mob that we would like to kill.<br>
<br>
What does this mean? It means we have to be able to mobilize.<br>
<br>
This is what I would like to see.  Say for one sunday we don't plan a raid.  People are encouraged to be on, but they can do thier own thing....xp, tradeskills, farm plat...whatever.  During this time, we have our raidleaders looking for things to kill.  <br>
<br>
Say they find Rhag 1 up.<br>
A call goes out to fed chat.  Rhag 1 is up, everyone come to SSra.  People finish up what they are doing and get a port there, in 20 minutes we are there and ready to start forming groups. Wishfull thinking?<br>
<br>
What needs to happen?  First off, I believe we need to nominate a few raid leaders.  A few obvious ones, such as Gotrik, Eldark, and Lachadan , (or maybe even me) come to mind...but a few more wouldn't hurt, but not more than 5 or 6.  These people would have the responsibility of calling a raid, and when they did, everyone would know that it would for sure happen, and that they should try as best they can to get there.  Hopefully, people would postpone thier more easily schedualed raid (kael, ToV, CT), and thier xp groups,  to get a chance at this harder to reach mob, with theoretically better loots.<br>
<br>
Of course, Participation would not be manditory.  I don't want any of this uber crap where we make people raid, and punish them if we don't.  I just want something more firm than &quot;Hey look, so-and-so is up...neat&quot;.<br>
<br>
Thoughts? <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87219>Reign Cloud</a> <BR>
