<br>
First, as long as it stays to a &quot;IF you're on, let's raid&quot; mentality, I'm all for it.  But if it turns into a &quot;everyone has to be online this day for so many hours&quot; situation, then I'll say &quot;Cya and good luck&quot;...and I'll go look for another guild. It's a damn game and there's no reason it should be treated like a job.<br>
<br>
Secondly, before any decision is made to call a raid, whoever is &quot;on duty&quot; that day (i.e. out looking for things to kill) better make damn sure there's enough people in the Federation that's online right then, and of the appropriate level, before even MENTIONING it in the Federation chat/guild chat.  A former guild I was in tried the &quot;if it's up, let's kill it&quot; thing...and we would get wiped EVERY SINGLE TIME because 1) there wasn't enough people online to make it work, 2) the appropriate classes weren't online to make it work, and 3) there weren't enough total levels online to make it work. It's a great idea, but it'll fail everytime if we try to force the square peg into the round hole, so to speak.<br>
