<br>
The idea of EXP groups on call is a great one.  This would be good for many reasons.<br>
<br>
You could arrange it like a signup raid so you know how many you have etc.  Example ok Sunday from noon est till 6pm we are going to have an on call raid.<br>
<br>
People can be online and do FED ONLY exp groups that way if something comes up you dont have to worry about leaving your group etc because the whole group knows in advance if something pops that we are mobilizing.  You get 5 or 6 said groups and you have a force on demand.<br>
<br>
Plus this way we are getting exp which we need anyways, and we are grouping with Fed members which in theory will be way better then the random pickup groups you would get elsewhere.<br>
<br>
This would also allow people to EXP in places like Charasis and maybe some of the other less frequented zones that are hard to get pickup groups in.<br>
<br>
If each group has a porter there would be no excuse to not have the ability to be at just about any zone within 10 minutes.<br>
<br>
One of the main issues is that everyone needs to know ahead of time that this is the plan, and they need to knmow their way around.  IMO everyone should either know, or have maps, to get to any zone in the game.  I'm not saying you should know every dungeon inside and out, but at least know the common. fastest travel routes.  You can learn this in very little time at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com.">www.eqatlas.com.</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
